class_description:
This class defines the Service Provider Interface (SPI)
 for the MessageDigest class, which provides the functionality
 of a message digest algorithm, such as MD5 or SHA. Message digests are
 secure one-way hash functions that take arbitrary-sized data and output a
 fixed-length hash value. All the abstract methods in this class must be implemented by a
 cryptographic service provider who wishes to supply the implementation
 of a particular message digest algorithm. Implementations are free to implement the Cloneable interface.
